@node section1 "Description"

DESCRIPTION
-----------


I  have  recently installed the wonderfull program 'Amidock' by Gary Knight
it's  quite  an  old  program  from  1991 but still extremely usefull.  The
program  is  along  the lines of toolsmanager and the like where you have a
line  of  iff  brushes that you click on once to run a certain program, the
brushes  that  come  with  the archive are now a little dated and so i have
taken  it  upon  myself  to  make some new brushes for it to bring it up to
date.   I  wanted  something  to  make  it  look  like it was part of Magic
Workbench  as  I  run  that amazing program as well, so armed with Personal
paint I started to create a small library of dock brushes.




@endnode
@node section2 "How It's Done"

HOW IT'S DONE
-------------


Easy,  just  run  PPaint,  open  some windows with Magic Workbench icons in
them,  do  a screen grab in PPaint and grab the icons as a brush, save them
to a directory and then sort them out into seperate directories later, it's
a  very tedious job and I hope that i'm not breaking any copyright rules by
doing this, hopefully not as the icons are freely distributable anyway.

@endnode

@node section3 "Distrubition and copyright etc."

DISTRIBUTION ETC
----------------

This  archive  and its contents is given away as "Logonware", this means if
you  like it enough to use it then you MUST call my bbs sometime and upload
a few files that have been of interest to you, The details are given at the
end  of  this doc file.  This file can be included in any Amiga magazine as
long  as  I  recieve  a  copy  free of charge, please contact my bbs for my
address, the same goes to any CD or PD collection, do what you like with it
but  dont  hold  me  responsible  for any damage caused by any of the files
included in this archive.

@endnode


